<paragraph id="513F1C42194DC53FF962FD49FC1CFCBE" blockId="33.[826,1441,659,773]" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis id="63F4C050194DC53FF962FD49FC0FFD13" box="[826,952,659,680]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin words 
<emphasis id="63F4C050194DC53FF9B4FD68FB92FD7C" box="[1004,1061,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">brevi</emphasis>
meaning short and 
<emphasis id="63F4C050194DC53FFF14FD69FA16FD73" box="[1356,1441,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">pinguis</emphasis>
meaning stout, referring to the unique shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
